{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e7ef73f7-2e2a-4d9a-b972-a5a533890dec","content":"Here's how to skip tests with a reason in each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n\n// For theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest(int x) { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nAll of these will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results and display the reason message in the test runner output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3f2bf0c3-45fe-4322-8547-76c19724fb6b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing tools.","outputTokens":264,"requestId":"843B:1B97B9:1E23495:217480B:6A0ACE7D"},"id":"195e89c2-e21a-41e1-9552-8a5ed2d994ec","timestamp":"2026-05-18T08:32:03.419Z","parentId":"9fff0c6c-ccc8-4015-82b6-6e25cfac3b23"}
